      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder [Player Name],

Iron Hearth sends word that [url=glossary:graven ashe]Graven Ashe[/url] rescinds your welcome within his walls. The Archon of War accuses you of treachery and sedition and demands that I hold you accountable with a public trial and execution. I reminded him that I am the sole arbiter of who runs afoul of the Overlord's legal code but assured him that I would investigate his claims thoroughly. 

Your inability to maintain this court's relationships with its allies disappoints me. Be warned that we all inevitably answer for our choices. You are no exception. 

Meanwhile, I understand that [url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url] has taken particular interest in you. I trust there is no need to illustrate the implications of his attention.

- [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator, Archon of Justice
</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder [Player Name],

Cacophony sends word that [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url] rescinds your invitation to their revels. The Archon of Secrets sent numerous compliments regarding your treachery and impetuousness, compliments I feel inclined to investigate thoroughly. 

Your inability to maintain this court's relationships with its allies - even those as base and abhorrent as the Chorus - disappoints me. Be warned that we all inevitably answer for our choices. You are no exception.

Meanwhile, I understand that [url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url] has taken particular interest in you. I trust there is no need to illustrate the implications of his attention.

- [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator, Archon of Justice
</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder [Player Name],

Calio informs me that your fledgling alliance of Tiersmen has collapsed upon itself. You knew well their fractiousness, yet you persisted in your attempts to coalesce them into a personal army. I hope that this failure neither terribly surprises nor disappoints you.

Your inability to wisely choose your allies disheartens me.

I understand that [url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url] has taken particular interest in you. I trust there is no need to illustrate the implications of his attention.

- [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator, Archon of Justice
</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder [Player Name],

I have received word that your former allies have rescinded your welcome among their camps. Accusations of treachery and sedition hound you. I receive daily demands that I hold you accountable with a public trial and execution. I have assured all that I would investigate these claims thoroughly. 

Be warned that we all inevitably answer for our choices. You are no exception.

In the meantime, I understand that [url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url] has taken particular interest in you. I trust there is no need to illustrate the implications of his attention.

- [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator, Archon of Justice
</DefaultText>
