    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>Archon [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url],

My service remains to the Overlord, to yourself and your court, and to the laws of [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]. That I could not continue abetting the Archon speaks less to my loyalty to the Overlord than it does his criminal behavior. 

I will continue my investigations from the shadows, and I assure you that all treachery will eventually be dragged into the light.

- Fatebinder [Player Name]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>Archon [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url],

Why did you pluck me from my prior circumstances and appoint me a Fatebinder if not for my judgment? If I could have both maintained an objective investigation and remained allies with the Archon, I would have. Unfortunately it could not be.

I assure you, Adjudicator, the inquiry continues apace. With [url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url]'s guidance, no shadow shall remain unsearched.

- Fatebinder [Player Name]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>Archon [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url],

This is merely the latest symptom of our warmasters' incompetence, completing a series that began with the stalling of the Conquest, continued into the [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Execution, and culminated with this ridiculous civil war. At minimum, the Archon is criminally incompetent. I suspect, however, more seditious motivations.

I could not continue to work against the interests of the Court. I will aid Archon [url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url] and remain in your humble service.

- Fatebinder [Player Name]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>Archon [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url],

I believed that neither the Archon of Secrets nor the Archon of War could be trusted to complete the Conquest. An alliance of the forces of the Tiers seemed the best path to uniting the peninsula under the Overlord's banner. I confess that I was mistaken. My loyalty to the Overlord remains unshaken, however.

I will work with [url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url] to continue my investigations into the machinations of the Archons. I hope that I again earn your esteem. 

- Fatebinder [Player Name]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>Archon [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url],

Why did you pluck me from my prior circumstances and appoint me a Fatebinder if not for my judgment? I believed that working with the Tiersmen would allow me to remain unbiased in fulfilling my obligations. Clearly I underestimated their self-indulgent, backbiting nature. 

I assure you, Adjudicator, the inquiry continues apace. With [url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url]'s guidance, no shadow shall remain unsearched.

- Fatebinder [Player Name]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>Archon [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url],

The Tiersmen, it turns out, are as prone to infighting and foolishness as the Archons of War and Secrets. Perhaps it was a mistake to trust them to follow orders and unite for their own survival. I would have thought that they would have learned from the mistakes that cost them the Tiers. 

I continue to work the court's interest, albeit with fewer resources at my disposal. I believe that [url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url] has a plan to help remedy that.

- Fatebinder [Player Name]</DefaultText>
